You don't even know I came to kill your hope.

[VERSE 2]
Cut into the apartments, up the stairs room to room,
Chasing down the echo of your silenced boom.
Shot cracks again, same flare over the hatch,
Not in these halls, you're up top watching the catch.
To the mountains' left side where you drew your lines,
I creep into your flank as your nerve unwinds.

[PRE-CHORUS 2]
