  {
    title: 'Friendly',
    lyrics: `[VERSE 1]
We were scavenging rooms in the pale apartments,
Picking through shadows, through dust and fragments.
Another crew showed up and said, "Friendly, it's okay,"
We loosened our guard, replied "friendly," then turned away.
Their "friendly" shots hit us, so sudden, so near,
Both of my friends dropped, then crawled, shaking with fear.
My family-in-arms still alive, calling for me,
Whispering "please, help me" in one breaking plea.

[CHORUS]
If I trust again, will it turn to pain,
Or is killing my trust a worse kind of chain?
Should one word, "friendly", poison every voice,
Or do I die keeping trust as my choice?

[VERSE 2]
I froze for a heartbeat, torn open inside,
Each plea was a weight I could not set aside.
The hallway lit up with a hail of gunfire,
Drove me to the window with one last desire.
I threw myself out through the open frame wide,
The world spun and slammed me on cement outside.
Now downed, I crawl slowly, keep my body low,
Their boots echo closer on concrete below.

[CHORUS]
If I trust again, will it turn to pain,
Or is killing my trust a worse kind of chain?
Should one word, "friendly",
poison every voice,
Or do I die keeping trust as my choice?

[VERSE 3]
I feel all our loot, every scrap that we own,
Still strapped to my body, now heavy as stone.
All the plans that we made, all the chances we chased,
Now shrink to these seconds I cannot replace.
Could we have moved softer, seen through their disguise,
Heard danger sit quiet behind friendly eyes?
Their footsteps grow nearer, I hold in my breath,
One silent heartbeat between me and death.

[FINAL CHORUS]
If I trust again, will it turn to pain,
Or is killing my trust a worse kind of chain?
Should one word, "friendly", poison every voice,
Or did I die keeping trust as my choice?`,
